<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="795" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/5063a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant
                                Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PAJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Peters</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PAJ1">Peters</persName></hi>: The Secretaries of the British and
                            French Embassies called upon me yesterday requesting that steps be taken
                            so that the publication of manifests of ships sailing from the United
                            States for Allied countries be discontinued.</p>
                        <p>I merely desire to bring these facts to your attention and to inquire
                            whether, in your opinion, it would be possible to take any steps looking
                            to the discontinuance of the publication of the manifests.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>